pullRequest.title: Impact analysis
pullRequest.bodyText: Completes IDETECT-1864 in providing Detect with the ability to run the Vulnerability Impact Analysis Tool.

commit.message: feat(impact-analysis): Added Vulnerability Impact Analysis tool.
fix(impact-analysis): Added code location name generation for impact analysis.
feat(impact-analysis): Added ability to upload impact analysis report.
refactor(impact-analysis): Moved service to separate package.
refactor(path-adapter): Removing PathAdapter because it was unused.
build(dependency): Switched from local to published version of com.synopsys:method-analyzer-core.
doc(impact-analysis): Added some doc to indicate the impact analysis can be enabled.

nodes.bodyText: Would prefer static creation methods like ImpactAnalysisUploadResult.success()
I don't love writing our json pojo's with these constructors but I'm not requesting they be changed, just wanted to note it.

nodes.bodyText: I question that these tests provide any tangible value and are worth the 'code liability' though there is something to be said about whether or not tests are considered 'code liability'.

commit.message: refactor(impact-analysis): Added named constructors to ImpactAnalysisUploadResult.
fix(impact-analysis): Impact Analysis report was being sent to the wrong output directory.
refactor(impact-analysis): Removed constructor ignored by Gson.
test(impact-analysis): Tested request creation rather than Gson.
refactor(impact-analysis): Made the constructor private for ImpactAnalysisUploadResult.
